fork

git clone <forked url>

open the cloned folder

git remote add upstream <main repo link>
git fetch upstream
git checkout main
git merge upstream/main

git push origin main

git add .
git commit -m "any message"
git config --global user.email "your email"
git config --global user.name "your name"
git commit -m "any message"

git push origin main
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
the files will be stored in your forked repository to update main repository :
Create a Pull Request (PR)
Switch to your forked repository on GitHub.
Click the "Pull requests" tab.
Click "New pull request".
Select the base repository and branch (main repository's branch where you want to merge your changes).
Base repository: The main repository (original repo).
Base branch: The branch in the main repo (commonly main or master).
Head repository: Your fork.
Head branch: The branch in your fork where your changes are.
Add a PR Title and Description
Provide a clear and concise title for the PR.
Add a detailed description explaining what changes you made and why they're important.
Include screenshots or references, if necessary.
Submit the PR
Click "Create pull request".
The maintainers of the main repository will now review your PR.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

to push the updated files from your computer to your github repo : git push origin main

to get the updated files from your github repo to your computer : git pull origin main
